1
00:00:36,266 --> 00:00:39,060
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

2
00:00:41,938 --> 00:00:43,523
-Oh, come on!
-What the hell?

3
00:00:51,239 --> 00:00:52,115
Oh dear.

4
00:00:52,198 --> 00:00:53,783
I'll take care of him.
No objections, right?

5
00:00:59,038 --> 00:01:00,582
Hold on!

6
00:01:01,958 --> 00:01:03,585
-Hold on.
-Excuse me, sir.

7
00:01:06,754 --> 00:01:08,590
Don't do this.

8
00:01:09,465 --> 00:01:10,550
Get off me!

9
00:01:12,594 --> 00:01:13,928
Oh no!

10
00:01:15,180 --> 00:01:16,139
Damn it.

11
00:01:18,391 --> 00:01:19,475
Don't go out.

12
00:01:20,852 --> 00:01:21,728
Hey.

13
00:01:23,855 --> 00:01:25,064
Sir!

14
00:01:25,148 --> 00:01:26,232
Please stop!

15
00:01:26,316 --> 00:01:27,233
That's enough!

16
00:01:27,317 --> 00:01:28,151
Come on!

17
00:01:28,234 --> 00:01:29,903
-Come on!
-I said enough!

18
00:01:29,986 --> 00:01:31,863
-Stop already!
-Jeez!

19
00:01:45,251 --> 00:01:46,836
-You didn't drink, right?
-Yeah.

20
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,879
Where's your car?

21
00:01:47,962 --> 00:01:49,005
-Over there.
-Let's go.

22
00:01:49,088 --> 00:01:49,923
Okay.

23
00:02:12,737 --> 00:02:14,530
-Write your screenplays like that!
-"Write your screenplays like that."

24
00:02:14,614 --> 00:02:16,908
Every word was dripping with sincerity.

25
00:02:17,492 --> 00:02:20,370
It was the best thing
you've written so far.

26
00:02:21,246 --> 00:02:22,747
Write your screenplays like that!

27
00:02:22,830 --> 00:02:24,707
"Write your screenplays like that!"

28
00:02:36,678 --> 00:02:37,887
Welcome.

29
00:02:53,027 --> 00:02:54,612
Where is everyone?

30
00:02:54,696 --> 00:02:55,530
Oh, well…

31
00:02:56,656 --> 00:02:58,157
The police came, and…

32
00:02:58,241 --> 00:03:00,034
I'm not really sure.

33
00:03:03,413 --> 00:03:04,747
This is for the window.

34
00:03:04,831 --> 00:03:07,083
It's 200,000 won.
Let me know if it's not enough.

35
00:03:08,751 --> 00:03:09,919
Oh, okay.

36
00:03:10,003 --> 00:03:10,962
Did you…

37
00:03:13,214 --> 00:03:14,257
throw that rock?

38
00:03:16,050 --> 00:03:17,176
Yes.

39
00:03:18,177 --> 00:03:19,012
Why?

40
00:03:21,431 --> 00:03:22,515
Because I was bored.

41
00:03:23,141 --> 00:03:23,975
Bored?

42
00:03:29,564 --> 00:03:33,401
"37, Hyowon 2-gil…"

43
00:03:35,820 --> 00:03:36,696
Occupation?

44
00:03:52,086 --> 00:03:52,920
Occupation?

45
00:03:57,550 --> 00:03:58,593
He's a film director.

46
00:04:04,265 --> 00:04:05,099
Who are you?

47
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,268
The producer in charge.

48
00:04:30,416 --> 00:04:31,334
Dong-man!

49
00:04:31,417 --> 00:04:32,627
-Dong-man!
-My goodness.

50
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:34,253
Dong-man, are you okay?

51
00:04:35,713 --> 00:04:36,923
Hey.

52
00:04:37,006 --> 00:04:38,716
They won't take him for the same reason.

53
00:04:39,342 --> 00:04:42,095
They said his blood pressure and pulse
are normal, so he's not an emergency case.

54
00:04:42,178 --> 00:04:43,554
Did you tell them he got beaten badly?

55
00:04:43,638 --> 00:04:44,931
I did!

56
00:04:45,014 --> 00:04:47,433
I said he got the crap beaten out of him
and to look at his face!

57
00:04:47,517 --> 00:04:49,227
He says he's dying from a concussion,

58
00:04:49,310 --> 00:04:51,771
but when they ask for his name,
he says, "Hwang Dong-man."

59
00:04:51,854 --> 00:04:54,107
He answers every single question
the nurse asks him.

60
00:04:54,774 --> 00:04:58,027
He needs to act like he's unconscious,
but he can't even do that!

61
00:04:59,237 --> 00:05:00,905
How can I get my own name wrong?

62
00:05:00,988 --> 00:05:02,115
That's not what I said!

63
00:05:02,198 --> 00:05:03,574
Just don't answer!

64
00:05:03,658 --> 00:05:05,743
Keep quiet and pretend to be unconscious!

65
00:05:05,827 --> 00:05:06,702
Jeez.

66
00:05:07,328 --> 00:05:08,454
Whatever.

67
00:05:08,538 --> 00:05:10,623
If they turn him away again,
I'll just take him home.

68
00:05:17,922 --> 00:05:21,008
Damn it, why can't you
just pretend you passed out?

69
00:05:21,092 --> 00:05:24,095
That's the only way
to get admitted into the ER!

70
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:25,805
That's embarrassing.

71
00:05:26,681 --> 00:05:28,683
How am I supposed to act?

72
00:05:29,809 --> 00:05:30,685
He's not hurt.

73
00:05:31,352 --> 00:05:32,395
He hasn't suffered enough.

74
00:05:33,604 --> 00:05:35,565
So, 120 over 80…

75
00:05:36,065 --> 00:05:38,109
What's your name, sir?

76
00:05:40,736 --> 00:05:41,863
Your name, sir.

77
00:05:42,947 --> 00:05:44,365
Your name.

78
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:53,082
Here. How many do you see?

79
00:05:54,250 --> 00:05:55,126
How many?

80
00:05:56,794 --> 00:05:59,213
Why would you get that right, you idiot?

81
00:05:59,297 --> 00:06:00,840
How can I get "two" wrong?

82
00:06:00,923 --> 00:06:03,509
Just take him home, all right? Damn it.

83
00:06:03,593 --> 00:06:05,678
They said he's not an emergency case!

84
00:06:05,761 --> 00:06:07,263
Fine, let's just take him home!

85
00:06:08,389 --> 00:06:09,807
-What's wrong?
-Hey!

86
00:06:09,891 --> 00:06:11,809
-Hey!
-Stop him!

87
00:06:11,893 --> 00:06:13,102
-Hey!
-No, wait!

88
00:06:19,317 --> 00:06:20,568
He sure stuffed himself.

89
00:06:25,281 --> 00:06:26,490
Do you have any water?

90
00:06:26,574 --> 00:06:27,617
Right away, sir.

91
00:06:48,387 --> 00:06:49,263
It's snowing.

92
00:06:55,811 --> 00:06:56,938
Here.

93
00:07:00,942 --> 00:07:01,984
Take it.

94
00:07:02,068 --> 00:07:03,069
Oh, thanks.

95
00:07:17,124 --> 00:07:18,209
I feel better now.

96
00:07:38,771 --> 00:07:41,065
I'll give you 10,000 won. Let's just go!

97
00:07:43,609 --> 00:07:44,652
I'll give you 50,000 won.

98
00:07:47,071 --> 00:07:48,698
You've got to be kidding me.

99
00:07:50,616 --> 00:07:51,450
Hello?

100
00:07:51,993 --> 00:07:53,911
It's not a concussion.
There's no need to go to the hospital.

101
00:07:53,995 --> 00:07:55,204
Doesn't even look like he's in pain.

102
00:07:56,038 --> 00:07:58,457
He's going nuts
trying to fish out a 500-won coin.

103
00:07:59,292 --> 00:08:00,459
Yeah, 500 won!

104
00:08:01,419 --> 00:08:03,796
Out of the sewer! Where he just threw up!

105
00:08:05,506 --> 00:08:08,134
-Come on, hold it up right.
-It's not even 50,000 won.

106
00:08:08,217 --> 00:08:09,635
It's 500 won.

107
00:08:09,719 --> 00:08:11,053
-He was feeling nauseous, and…
-Lower, lower.

108
00:08:11,137 --> 00:08:12,805
-For goodness's sake.
-To your six o'clock.

109
00:08:12,888 --> 00:08:13,723
Good.

110
00:08:17,101 --> 00:08:18,019
What did he say?

111
00:09:13,824 --> 00:09:15,368
Park Gyeong-se, come out!

112
00:09:19,121 --> 00:09:20,289
I said come out!

113
00:09:22,208 --> 00:09:23,793
Damn it.

114
00:09:40,434 --> 00:09:43,145
I got cut off
because I was getting my ass kicked,

115
00:09:43,229 --> 00:09:44,522
but let me finish what I was saying.

116
00:09:45,856 --> 00:09:48,693
I had a lot prepared,
but none of it matters now.

117
00:09:49,985 --> 00:09:51,153
I'll just get to the point.

118
00:09:53,406 --> 00:09:54,240
The Eight Club?

119
00:09:55,825 --> 00:09:57,034
Forget it. I'm out.

120
00:09:58,244 --> 00:09:59,745
That's for you shiny people.

121
00:10:01,372 --> 00:10:03,833
I chose to live a worthless life…

122
00:10:06,085 --> 00:10:07,920
so what's The Eight Club to me?

123
00:10:09,171 --> 00:10:10,214
I'm sorry

124
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,842
for sticking around when I wasn't wanted.

125
00:10:14,635 --> 00:10:16,512
You win at cutting down people with words.

126
00:10:17,638 --> 00:10:19,807
I'll give you that.

127
00:10:20,641 --> 00:10:21,809
But you know what?

128
00:10:22,685 --> 00:10:25,312
If I put my mind to it,
I can cut people down too.

129
00:10:26,063 --> 00:10:27,273
I just choose not to.

130
00:10:28,399 --> 00:10:29,275
Then do it.

131
00:10:30,526 --> 00:10:31,360
Go ahead!

132
00:10:33,279 --> 00:10:34,613
My jokes

133
00:10:35,322 --> 00:10:37,074
are just for blowing off steam,

134
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:39,952
not cutting people down.

135
00:10:43,873 --> 00:10:44,874
Hey, let me ask you something.

136
00:10:46,709 --> 00:10:48,627
Why have you been so mean to me?

137
00:10:49,670 --> 00:10:51,380
You don't treat the others like that.

138
00:10:52,089 --> 00:10:54,842
But you always tear into my films
like a maniac.

139
00:10:55,843 --> 00:10:57,094
People ask, you know.

140
00:10:58,095 --> 00:11:00,639
"Why does Hwang Dong-man
hate Park Gyeong-se so much?"

141
00:11:02,808 --> 00:11:03,893
You must have a reason.

142
00:11:05,978 --> 00:11:07,605
A reason why you hate me so much.

143
00:11:07,688 --> 00:11:10,483
I only liked Hye-jin for a short time.

144
00:11:10,566 --> 00:11:11,567
Not that, damn it!

145
00:11:15,070 --> 00:11:17,323
There's got to be a reason
why you hate me!

146
00:11:22,453 --> 00:11:24,205
Because you hated me first.

147
00:11:28,792 --> 00:11:30,669
Why made you hate me so much?

148
00:11:58,739 --> 00:12:01,033
As of today, I'm leaving The Eight Club.

149
00:12:02,826 --> 00:12:05,329
I'm sorry I stuck around for so long
without taking a hint.

150
00:12:05,412 --> 00:12:06,622
THE EIGHT CLUB

151
00:12:06,705 --> 00:12:08,374
I'm leaving my crap behind.

152
00:12:09,208 --> 00:12:10,209
Just make a new group chat.

153
00:12:16,090 --> 00:12:17,258
THE EIGHT CLUB
LEAVE THIS CHAT?

154
00:12:21,554 --> 00:12:22,555
LEAVE

155
00:12:36,902 --> 00:12:37,987
HWANG DONG-MAN HAS LEFT THE CHAT

156
00:12:39,405 --> 00:12:40,322
INVITE HWANG DONG-MAN TO THIS CHAT?

157
00:12:40,406 --> 00:12:41,240
CONFIRM

158
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:46,328
The Eight Club
isn't something you can join

159
00:12:46,412 --> 00:12:48,080
and leave as you--

160
00:12:48,163 --> 00:12:49,206
HWANG DONG-MAN HAS LEFT THE CHAT

161
00:12:49,290 --> 00:12:50,374
Goddamn it.

162
00:12:53,127 --> 00:12:54,211
Jeez.

163
00:12:54,295 --> 00:12:56,880
HWANG DONG-MAN HAS LEFT THE CHAT

164
00:13:06,974 --> 00:13:09,184
They used to be inseparable.

165
00:13:10,227 --> 00:13:12,062
I don't know how they ended up like this.

166
00:13:12,146 --> 00:13:14,273
What? They used to be close?

167
00:13:40,382 --> 00:13:42,217
Damn it.

168
00:15:15,310 --> 00:15:17,354
I thought you threw up a lot.

169
00:15:17,938 --> 00:15:19,273
I need to fill up again

170
00:15:20,399 --> 00:15:21,400
since I threw up a lot.

171
00:15:29,992 --> 00:15:32,244
"If I can't prove myself by succeeding,

172
00:15:33,203 --> 00:15:35,205
I'll prove myself by falling apart."

173
00:15:36,290 --> 00:15:39,334
I feel proud
because I really fell apart today.

174
00:15:39,835 --> 00:15:43,130
It's the feeling of a day well spent.

175
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:49,219
Doing it alone is exhausting.

176
00:15:50,804 --> 00:15:53,974
It's less exhausting when you have someone
telling you whether it's good or not.

177
00:15:56,477 --> 00:15:57,394
I'll stay by your side

178
00:15:58,020 --> 00:15:58,979
and watch you.

179
00:16:12,284 --> 00:16:13,869
Why do you keep covering it?

180
00:16:13,952 --> 00:16:14,787
Oh, well…

181
00:16:15,704 --> 00:16:16,538
This thing

182
00:16:17,414 --> 00:16:19,041
does that sometimes.

183
00:16:20,542 --> 00:16:21,627
I feel good.

184
00:16:22,628 --> 00:16:23,754
I'm sure I feel good.

185
00:16:24,922 --> 00:16:26,048
But the watch is red.

186
00:16:28,634 --> 00:16:30,385
When it was snowing earlier,

187
00:16:30,969 --> 00:16:33,889
the watch vibrated,
and I didn't even question it.

188
00:16:33,972 --> 00:16:36,308
I figured it'd be green.

189
00:16:37,267 --> 00:16:38,477
But it was red.

190
00:16:41,188 --> 00:16:42,106
I was curious

191
00:16:43,148 --> 00:16:44,066
and looked at it.

192
00:16:45,234 --> 00:16:46,276
It said, "lonely."

193
00:16:49,196 --> 00:16:51,824
So I thought,
"I guess I like being lonely."

194
00:16:52,908 --> 00:16:56,453
I guess it's no different from me

195
00:16:56,537 --> 00:16:58,622
liking things
like "destruction" and "hate."

196
00:16:59,706 --> 00:17:00,707
I'm the kind of guy

197
00:17:01,291 --> 00:17:03,168
who's anxious by default,

198
00:17:03,252 --> 00:17:05,337
so my watch turns red all the time.

199
00:17:05,420 --> 00:17:07,089
But when it does,

200
00:17:07,172 --> 00:17:09,925
I feel like I'm being rude
to the person in front of me.

201
00:17:10,551 --> 00:17:11,718
Don't you agree?

202
00:17:14,972 --> 00:17:16,640
If this ever hits the market,

203
00:17:17,224 --> 00:17:19,143
it'll destroy all relationships.

204
00:17:20,853 --> 00:17:22,437
Imagine couples wearing this.

205
00:17:23,856 --> 00:17:26,316
They claim to be in love and such,

206
00:17:26,942 --> 00:17:27,860
but it's not love.

207
00:17:31,029 --> 00:17:32,573
They say "love" doesn't appear.

208
00:17:34,199 --> 00:17:37,202
Because "love" is a concept,
not an emotion.

209
00:17:38,412 --> 00:17:39,746
Oh.

210
00:17:40,831 --> 00:17:41,832
I see.

211
00:17:42,499 --> 00:17:44,209
"Love" isn't an emotion.

212
00:17:44,293 --> 00:17:49,173
They say it just shows things like
"excited," "thrilled," or "nervous."

213
00:17:50,048 --> 00:17:52,426
What you're feeling in the moment.

214
00:17:53,343 --> 00:17:54,178
Right.

215
00:17:54,803 --> 00:17:56,305
How would you even detect love?

216
00:17:57,139 --> 00:17:58,849
Everyone's definition of love
is different.

217
00:18:00,142 --> 00:18:01,185
No wonder.

218
00:18:02,186 --> 00:18:05,314
The word "love"
always made me feel frustrated.

219
00:18:05,939 --> 00:18:08,025
Everyone keeps going on about love,

220
00:18:08,108 --> 00:18:10,360
so I wondered if I was the only one
who didn't know that feeling.

221
00:18:11,069 --> 00:18:14,573
I mean, I understand what it means
to long for or miss someone.

222
00:18:15,574 --> 00:18:17,826
But I kept wondering,
"What exactly is love?"

223
00:18:17,910 --> 00:18:19,953
"What is love?"

224
00:18:22,039 --> 00:18:22,956
What a huge relief.

225
00:18:26,710 --> 00:18:28,003
Now that I know it doesn't show "love,"

226
00:18:29,254 --> 00:18:31,131
I suddenly feel like I can trust it again.

227
00:18:33,383 --> 00:18:34,218
In that case,

228
00:18:35,344 --> 00:18:37,179
I can roll up my sleeve.

229
00:18:37,679 --> 00:18:39,598
Man, I was so worried

230
00:18:39,681 --> 00:18:41,475
that "love" would suddenly show up…

231
00:18:46,980 --> 00:18:48,607
I mean…

232
00:18:48,690 --> 00:18:49,524
What I mean is…

233
00:18:50,192 --> 00:18:52,027
Like a glitch, you know?

234
00:18:52,694 --> 00:18:54,947
I mean, I guess it's possible

235
00:18:55,530 --> 00:18:59,201
to love someone for a split second, right?

236
00:19:00,410 --> 00:19:02,287
Because we can't control how we feel.

237
00:19:09,253 --> 00:19:11,505
Anyway, there's no "love."

238
00:19:24,017 --> 00:19:24,851
By the way,

239
00:19:25,811 --> 00:19:26,853
can I text you?

240
00:19:27,771 --> 00:19:28,605
Of course.

241
00:19:30,732 --> 00:19:31,984
Can I text you anytime?

242
00:19:32,818 --> 00:19:33,694
Absolutely.

243
00:19:36,113 --> 00:19:37,572
I have no one to talk to now.

244
00:19:41,702 --> 00:19:43,578
-Can I really text you anytime?
-Yes, really.

245
00:19:44,121 --> 00:19:45,205
Okay.

246
00:20:09,354 --> 00:20:10,731
You'd better not beat me up again.

247
00:20:11,356 --> 00:20:12,899
How many times do I have to tell you?

248
00:20:12,983 --> 00:20:15,610
I'm not taking it
because your punches are stronger.

249
00:20:23,618 --> 00:20:25,329
You stuff your face like that
in public too?

250
00:20:37,799 --> 00:20:38,842
WE SELL GIMBAP

251
00:20:54,232 --> 00:20:57,569
EMPLOYMENT HISTORY RECORD
BYEON EUN-A, ADMIN ASSISTANT AT CHOI FILM

252
00:21:09,414 --> 00:21:10,957
What's he doing here?

253
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:16,421
Why do I have a bad feeling about you
being here so early?

254
00:21:19,466 --> 00:21:20,675
The doors are opening.

255
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:30,268
Your official statement
was nice and heartfelt.

256
00:21:31,978 --> 00:21:33,021
So what is it?

257
00:21:33,105 --> 00:21:34,898
-Did some other problem come up?
-The doors are closing.

258
00:21:44,366 --> 00:21:45,200
Get in.

259
00:21:50,914 --> 00:21:52,457
The doors are closing.

260
00:21:57,629 --> 00:21:59,005
Did you not go home last night?

261
00:22:00,507 --> 00:22:01,591
I did.

262
00:22:02,592 --> 00:22:03,969
Then why is your outfit the same?

263
00:22:05,804 --> 00:22:07,139
It's a different outfit.

264
00:22:23,447 --> 00:22:25,407
-Good morning, Mr. Choi.
-Hey.

265
00:22:26,074 --> 00:22:27,576
-Hello.
-Hello.

266
00:22:27,659 --> 00:22:28,994
Hello, yourself.

267
00:22:33,456 --> 00:22:35,792
Showing up this early means he's on edge.

268
00:22:35,876 --> 00:22:36,918
Who is he?

269
00:22:37,002 --> 00:22:38,461
The CEO of Oh Jeong-hui's agency.

270
00:22:43,133 --> 00:22:43,967
So?

271
00:22:44,634 --> 00:22:45,719
Did you find her daughter?

272
00:22:47,262 --> 00:22:48,096
Sorry?

273
00:22:50,265 --> 00:22:51,391
Where's your head at?

274
00:22:51,474 --> 00:22:53,518
I asked if you found
Oh Jeong-hui's daughter.

275
00:22:56,313 --> 00:22:57,147
Yes.

276
00:23:02,694 --> 00:23:03,820
Then what's with that look?

277
00:23:06,156 --> 00:23:07,157
What is it?

278
00:23:08,867 --> 00:23:11,161
Is her daughter absolutely furious?

279
00:23:14,789 --> 00:23:16,041
Damn, you're making me nervous!

280
00:23:16,124 --> 00:23:17,375
What is it?

281
00:23:19,002 --> 00:23:19,961
No.

282
00:23:20,545 --> 00:23:21,796
She's not furious.

283
00:23:23,089 --> 00:23:25,759
OH JEONG-HUI REFUTES CLAIMS
SHE NEGLECTED HER DAUGHTER

284
00:23:29,638 --> 00:23:31,932
"ALTHOUGH MS. OH WAS UNABLE TO BE
WITH HER DAUGHTER UNTIL THE END,

285
00:23:32,015 --> 00:23:34,351
SHE SOUGHT TO MAINTAIN THEIR RELATIONSHIP
EVEN AFTER THE DIVORCE."

286
00:23:37,979 --> 00:23:40,065
Just beg her to spare you.

287
00:23:40,148 --> 00:23:41,858
Get on your knees if you have to!

288
00:23:51,409 --> 00:23:52,827
The doors are closing.

289
00:24:32,534 --> 00:24:34,286
WEATHER MAKER
BY HWANG DONG-MAN

290
00:24:45,213 --> 00:24:47,257
Eun-a sent me her revision notes.

291
00:24:48,341 --> 00:24:49,426
And damn,

292
00:24:49,509 --> 00:24:51,094
she did an amazing job.

293
00:24:52,220 --> 00:24:53,096
It's pissing me off.

294
00:24:55,098 --> 00:24:57,100
There's a mountain of revisions to make,

295
00:24:58,476 --> 00:25:00,061
and she's right about all of it.

296
00:25:00,729 --> 00:25:02,188
Do you look blank now?

297
00:25:03,023 --> 00:25:04,399
This is so damn embarrassing.

298
00:25:04,983 --> 00:25:06,943
Stop crying and come out.
I'll treat you to barbecue.

299
00:25:09,029 --> 00:25:10,822
It has to be Jang Mi-ran, no matter what.

300
00:25:11,406 --> 00:25:14,075
I was up all night worrying
she'd turn it down right away.

301
00:25:14,701 --> 00:25:17,746
Then I texted her to read my screenplay,
and she called right away

302
00:25:18,496 --> 00:25:19,331
and suggested we meet.

303
00:25:20,165 --> 00:25:20,999
With you.

304
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:23,626
Jang Mi-ran knows me?

305
00:25:24,919 --> 00:25:26,087
I doubt she even knows my name.

306
00:25:26,171 --> 00:25:29,257
She said she saw you
arguing with Gyeong-se in front of Agit.

307
00:25:33,636 --> 00:25:36,598
Goodness, has she fallen for me?

308
00:25:37,599 --> 00:25:38,808
Oh boy.

309
00:25:39,768 --> 00:25:42,354
She must hold a lot of resentment
toward Park Gyeong-se.

310
00:25:43,313 --> 00:25:46,149
If I had said everything
I prepared that day,

311
00:25:46,232 --> 00:25:47,484
it would've been game over.

312
00:25:49,069 --> 00:25:51,112
-Is she okay, by the way?
-What do you mean?

313
00:25:53,531 --> 00:25:55,200
About Oh Jeong-hui's real daughter.

314
00:25:56,034 --> 00:25:56,910
I mean,

315
00:25:57,577 --> 00:25:58,828
how's that Jang Mi-ran's problem?

316
00:25:59,662 --> 00:26:00,789
Don't bring it up later, okay?

317
00:26:00,872 --> 00:26:01,873
Why would I do that?

318
00:26:08,380 --> 00:26:09,339
Welcome.

319
00:26:10,048 --> 00:26:10,882
Wait.

320
00:26:12,467 --> 00:26:13,760
Jun-hwan.

321
00:26:13,843 --> 00:26:14,803
Hey.

322
00:26:15,428 --> 00:26:17,806
It's been a while. Good to see you.

323
00:26:18,306 --> 00:26:19,891
I heard you won the grant.

324
00:26:19,974 --> 00:26:20,892
Congratulations.

325
00:26:21,393 --> 00:26:23,061
Oh, it's nothing.

326
00:26:23,144 --> 00:26:24,521
All that hard work paid off.

327
00:26:25,980 --> 00:26:27,107
It's just the beginning.

328
00:26:31,277 --> 00:26:32,153
It's been a while, Dong-man.

329
00:26:34,614 --> 00:26:35,490
Yeah, it has.

330
00:26:36,783 --> 00:26:38,410
I was wondering how you were doing.

331
00:26:39,661 --> 00:26:40,537
I'm doing fine.

332
00:26:46,668 --> 00:26:47,669
What brings you here?

333
00:26:48,253 --> 00:26:50,130
Oh, I'm meeting Gi-yeong here.

334
00:26:50,213 --> 00:26:51,339
I see.

335
00:26:54,384 --> 00:26:55,760
-Excuse me.
-Sure.

336
00:26:57,804 --> 00:26:58,972
Hello?

337
00:26:59,848 --> 00:27:00,682
Yes, I see.

338
00:27:05,228 --> 00:27:06,104
Can we go somewhere else?

339
00:27:07,230 --> 00:27:08,690
But we're meeting her here.

340
00:27:15,196 --> 00:27:17,073
Seeing that jerk's face
pissed me right off.

341
00:27:18,992 --> 00:27:21,453
I've always thought
he was terrible at writing,

342
00:27:22,036 --> 00:27:24,330
even back when I was mentoring him
in film school.

343
00:27:24,831 --> 00:27:27,000
I've never seen anyone write
so badly and so cowardly.

344
00:27:29,419 --> 00:27:31,254
There's no substance in his writing.

345
00:27:32,172 --> 00:27:35,467
Instead, he obsesses over font styles
and line spacing like some pervert.

346
00:27:36,176 --> 00:27:38,052
He's an idiot who puts effort
into crap like that.

347
00:27:39,512 --> 00:27:41,723
I got pissed while reading his screenplay.

348
00:27:41,806 --> 00:27:45,643
He's the first bastard to make me think
I could commit murder.

349
00:27:45,727 --> 00:27:47,020
I feel attacked.

350
00:27:47,103 --> 00:27:49,522
I'm one of those idiots
who obsess over fonts now.

351
00:27:49,606 --> 00:27:51,274
Oh jeez. Have you lost your mind?

352
00:27:51,357 --> 00:27:54,068
When I like the font,
I feel like I like the writing more.

353
00:27:57,572 --> 00:27:58,656
Everyone is crazy.

354
00:27:59,157 --> 00:28:01,326
Investing three billion won
in a guy like him,

355
00:28:02,202 --> 00:28:04,162
and the production company
wanting to make it.

356
00:28:07,499 --> 00:28:09,250
Hye-jin's company is producing it.

357
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:14,422
I'm just telling you so you won't slip up.

358
00:28:17,258 --> 00:28:18,343
It doesn't matter.

359
00:28:19,385 --> 00:28:21,221
I'm not in The Eight Club anymore.

360
00:28:34,067 --> 00:28:35,902
-Have you been well?
-Yeah.

361
00:28:37,070 --> 00:28:38,238
Do you have a producer lined up?

362
00:28:38,321 --> 00:28:39,447
No, not yet.

363
00:28:40,073 --> 00:28:41,991
No producer at Kopark Film
fits the schedule.

364
00:28:42,617 --> 00:28:45,912
Producers work back and forth
between Choi Film and Kopark Film.

365
00:28:46,496 --> 00:28:50,375
But the only good producer at Choi Film
is Producer Hyo-jin.

366
00:28:51,042 --> 00:28:52,043
What do you mean?

367
00:28:52,126 --> 00:28:53,461
There's Producer Byeon Eun-a.

368
00:28:53,962 --> 00:28:55,588
There are lots of capable people.

369
00:28:55,672 --> 00:28:57,048
Well, Producer Byeon Eun-a

370
00:28:57,799 --> 00:29:00,093
hasn't done much
to be considered a producer.

371
00:29:01,052 --> 00:29:03,429
What do you mean?
She's developed a handful of projects.

372
00:29:03,513 --> 00:29:06,224
Do you know how many she's saved
from being thrown out?

373
00:29:06,307 --> 00:29:07,308
That's what I don't like.

374
00:29:08,726 --> 00:29:12,188
It feels like whatever she picks is a dud.

375
00:29:13,439 --> 00:29:15,483
I hear she only goes for stuff
that's about to get tossed.

376
00:29:16,150 --> 00:29:17,652
You know, the ones below her level.

377
00:29:19,654 --> 00:29:21,656
Like some kind of underdog solidarity.

378
00:29:22,448 --> 00:29:23,700
No, that's not fair.

379
00:29:23,783 --> 00:29:26,452
Established directors
have their own producers in charge.

380
00:29:26,536 --> 00:29:30,248
Producer Byeon is just starting out,
so she works with a different pool.

381
00:29:32,333 --> 00:29:33,585
You shouldn't put it like that.

382
00:29:35,503 --> 00:29:37,005
Right, well…

383
00:29:37,922 --> 00:29:38,756
That's just how I see it.

384
00:29:42,969 --> 00:29:43,928
Dong-man,

385
00:29:45,430 --> 00:29:47,181
how come you're not making films?

386
00:29:51,185 --> 00:29:52,312
You think I'm choosing not to?

387
00:30:01,029 --> 00:30:02,071
Hi!

388
00:30:03,740 --> 00:30:05,283
Oh, you're here.

389
00:30:20,423 --> 00:30:21,591
Hello.

390
00:30:38,733 --> 00:30:40,735
What qualifies as a good poem?

391
00:30:45,740 --> 00:30:48,451
The ones experts recommend
are all so hard to understand.

392
00:30:55,583 --> 00:30:56,459
A poem…

393
00:30:59,170 --> 00:31:00,505
makes sense once you memorize it.

394
00:31:04,425 --> 00:31:05,927
You won't get it just by reading it.

395
00:31:21,317 --> 00:31:25,071
I've never met anyone who speaks so well
but is so bad at filming.

396
00:31:25,154 --> 00:31:27,156
Honestly, I didn't like the screenplay.

397
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:28,241
I know, right?

398
00:31:28,324 --> 00:31:31,160
He said he'd explain it in person,
so I met him.

399
00:31:31,244 --> 00:31:32,870
I almost died laughing that day

400
00:31:32,954 --> 00:31:34,872
because he was so hilarious.

401
00:31:35,707 --> 00:31:37,792
I thought, "Was I wrong about it?"

402
00:31:38,584 --> 00:31:40,294
-I was fooled.
-You were fooled.

403
00:31:40,378 --> 00:31:41,796
Everyone does, all the time.

404
00:31:41,879 --> 00:31:43,881
You know the scene
where I had to saw my arm off?

405
00:31:43,965 --> 00:31:45,133
Guess how many takes it took.

406
00:31:48,094 --> 00:31:49,220
Cut!

407
00:31:49,303 --> 00:31:50,555
Let's try one more time.

408
00:31:50,638 --> 00:31:52,765
-The emotion's good, but…
-Scene 8, shot 7, take 17.

409
00:31:52,849 --> 00:31:54,308
Show me rage in the arm
that's still attached,

410
00:31:54,392 --> 00:31:56,185
and sadness in the other. Action!

411
00:31:57,270 --> 00:31:58,229
Cut!

412
00:31:58,312 --> 00:31:59,522
It looks like you're playing the violin.

413
00:32:00,732 --> 00:32:04,068
Cut! Can you add
about 10-won worth of sadness?

414
00:32:05,737 --> 00:32:06,654
Cut!

415
00:32:07,155 --> 00:32:08,156
Action!

416
00:32:11,534 --> 00:32:12,535
He said I lacked soul.

417
00:32:13,327 --> 00:32:15,329
Who has a soul
when they're sawing their own arm off?

418
00:32:15,413 --> 00:32:17,582
Who in their right mind
would saw their arm off?

419
00:32:18,082 --> 00:32:23,212
I kept sawing like I was actually
cutting off my own arm.

420
00:32:23,296 --> 00:32:26,215
I kept going until I was half-dead
and the sun came up.

421
00:32:30,344 --> 00:32:31,512
Cut.

422
00:32:33,181 --> 00:32:34,307
That's good for now.

423
00:32:34,390 --> 00:32:36,684
Let's call it a day here.
Good work, everyone.

424
00:32:37,226 --> 00:32:39,145
-Good job.
-Great work today.

425
00:32:40,313 --> 00:32:41,397
Can you get the right side?

426
00:32:51,157 --> 00:32:52,533
It felt like I was missing an arm.

427
00:32:54,202 --> 00:32:55,536
I couldn't feel it.

428
00:32:57,789 --> 00:32:59,540
I really sawed it off

429
00:33:00,291 --> 00:33:01,250
in my head.

430
00:33:02,835 --> 00:33:05,046
After that, I can't really use
my left arm anymore.

431
00:33:05,129 --> 00:33:06,339
I'm still like this.

432
00:33:11,469 --> 00:33:13,805
After all that method acting,

433
00:33:13,888 --> 00:33:18,101
Sister Vengeance was roasted online
as Tone-deaf Sister Vengeance.

434
00:33:18,726 --> 00:33:20,228
After that, whenever I see a weird scene,

435
00:33:20,311 --> 00:33:22,980
I get pissed because I know
it'll make me look like an idiot.

436
00:33:23,064 --> 00:33:25,650
And how many screenplays start off strong
but fall flat by the end?

437
00:33:25,733 --> 00:33:29,237
A smart, put-together woman
suddenly turns into a moron by the end.

438
00:33:29,904 --> 00:33:31,572
I'd stay up all night wondering

439
00:33:31,656 --> 00:33:34,242
how I could channel my inner moron
to play the role.

440
00:33:35,535 --> 00:33:37,870
Then I thought,
"Forget it. I'll write one myself."

441
00:33:38,496 --> 00:33:43,543
"I'll write one myself instead of living
at the mercy of garbage screenplays."

442
00:33:44,585 --> 00:33:45,545
Why don't you come to my class?

443
00:33:47,046 --> 00:33:48,631
No, I don't want to learn.

444
00:33:49,215 --> 00:33:51,175
Nothing's more boring than formal writing.

445
00:33:51,259 --> 00:33:54,178
I hate hearing about crap
like authenticity and story structure.

446
00:33:54,262 --> 00:33:56,722
You just have to write recklessly
and perform recklessly.

447
00:33:56,806 --> 00:33:58,182
-You're right.
-Right?

448
00:33:58,266 --> 00:33:59,934
-You have to be reckless.
-Exactly.

449
00:34:00,017 --> 00:34:00,893
Here's to being reckless.

450
00:34:00,977 --> 00:34:02,311
-Reckless!
-Reckless!

451
00:34:03,437 --> 00:34:05,356
Is one guy writing all the screenplays
in this country?

452
00:34:05,439 --> 00:34:07,024
How are they all the same?

453
00:34:07,108 --> 00:34:09,819
Then they ask the actor
if they can show another side.

454
00:34:09,902 --> 00:34:13,906
-Fetch me a different screenplay, then!
-Fetch it.

455
00:34:13,990 --> 00:34:16,075
-Fetch me a drink.
-Oh, okay.

456
00:34:18,536 --> 00:34:19,829
"Write your screenplays like that!"

457
00:34:19,912 --> 00:34:22,206
When you said that,

458
00:34:23,166 --> 00:34:25,668
my arm started twitching.

459
00:34:25,751 --> 00:34:28,171
Like a dead person
suddenly opening their eyes.

460
00:34:28,254 --> 00:34:29,755
It kept twitching.

461
00:34:31,382 --> 00:34:35,094
You know what
Park Gyeong-se's nickname used to be?

462
00:34:35,178 --> 00:34:36,429
What?

463
00:34:36,512 --> 00:34:37,680
"Watermelon Licker."

464
00:34:38,264 --> 00:34:40,474
He just needs to crack into it

465
00:34:40,558 --> 00:34:43,519
and at least give the audience a taste,

466
00:34:43,603 --> 00:34:44,645
but he can't.

467
00:34:44,729 --> 00:34:47,607
He just keeps carefully

468
00:34:48,149 --> 00:34:49,734
licking at it.

469
00:34:49,817 --> 00:34:53,321
Please stop licking it
and give us a taste already.

470
00:34:53,404 --> 00:34:54,363
That's what I'm saying.

471
00:34:54,447 --> 00:34:58,117
It's a sweet, juicy watermelon,
but he says,

472
00:34:58,201 --> 00:35:00,161
"I can't cut into this.
This is the best I can do."

473
00:35:00,244 --> 00:35:02,371
"Let's all give it a lick.
You'll feel the juice."

474
00:35:02,455 --> 00:35:03,414
What the hell?

475
00:35:03,998 --> 00:35:05,708
Oh? My goodness.

476
00:35:05,791 --> 00:35:06,792
It's moving again.

477
00:35:07,418 --> 00:35:09,212
It's twitching.

478
00:35:13,799 --> 00:35:15,468
Park Gyeong-se is a bastard
Damn Gyeong-se is a bastard

479
00:35:15,551 --> 00:35:17,261
He turns actors into morons

480
00:35:17,345 --> 00:35:19,931
What's my talent?

481
00:35:20,014 --> 00:35:21,349
Licking watermelons

482
00:35:21,933 --> 00:35:23,267
-Licking watermelons
-Licking watermelons

483
00:35:23,351 --> 00:35:24,977
Licking watermelons

484
00:35:25,061 --> 00:35:27,271
Licking… Oh!

485
00:35:30,691 --> 00:35:31,525
Holy crap.

486
00:36:03,557 --> 00:36:05,309
Are you trying to scare me with bad news?

487
00:36:05,935 --> 00:36:07,061
Why are you stalling?

488
00:36:10,356 --> 00:36:12,358
She changed her name

489
00:36:13,192 --> 00:36:15,778
from Byeon Si-on to Byeon Eun-a.

490
00:36:18,239 --> 00:36:19,907
-"Eun-a"?
-Yes.

491
00:36:22,910 --> 00:36:26,664
And she turned out to be closer
than I thought.

492
00:36:28,124 --> 00:36:29,375
She works at…

493
00:36:32,420 --> 00:36:33,963
Choi Film.

494
00:36:34,797 --> 00:36:37,466
I went there just in case,

495
00:36:38,634 --> 00:36:42,013
but no one seemed to know
that she's your daughter.

496
00:36:42,847 --> 00:36:46,392
If they knew, I don't think Mr. Choi
would have made such a fuss

497
00:36:46,475 --> 00:36:48,394
to find your daughter.

498
00:36:48,477 --> 00:36:50,771
And if he knew she was your daughter,

499
00:36:52,231 --> 00:36:53,482
would he treat her so badly?

500
00:36:55,985 --> 00:36:59,905
It's to the point where you almost wonder
if she's unaware of who her mother is.

501
00:36:59,989 --> 00:37:01,407
No one around her has any idea.

502
00:37:04,410 --> 00:37:08,205
She started as a contract admin assistant
and then went full-time.

503
00:37:08,831 --> 00:37:12,585
Considering that she worked similar jobs
after graduating high school,

504
00:37:13,878 --> 00:37:16,339
I don't think
she intentionally joined Choi Film.

505
00:37:19,008 --> 00:37:21,594
That man didn't even send her to college?

506
00:37:26,182 --> 00:37:28,684
Mr. Byeon Jae-su passed away in 2008,

507
00:37:29,769 --> 00:37:32,563
so she lives with her grandmother now.

508
00:37:35,691 --> 00:37:36,692
What grandmother?

509
00:37:37,693 --> 00:37:40,279
Both of her grandmothers have passed away.

510
00:37:40,863 --> 00:37:42,114
The thing is…

511
00:37:43,657 --> 00:37:46,160
Mr. Byeon Jae-su remarried--

512
00:37:46,243 --> 00:37:47,620
I know that.

513
00:37:47,703 --> 00:37:48,746
So…

514
00:37:49,538 --> 00:37:51,624
it's his second wife's…

515
00:37:53,084 --> 00:37:54,377
mother.

516
00:37:55,044 --> 00:37:58,047
She's living with her step-grandmother.

517
00:38:05,513 --> 00:38:07,264
Grandma, put it in here.

518
00:38:09,683 --> 00:38:11,644
They've been living together

519
00:38:12,269 --> 00:38:14,647
since Mr. Byeon remarried when she was 11.

520
00:38:15,940 --> 00:38:18,526
Even after he passed away
when she was in middle school,

521
00:38:19,151 --> 00:38:21,904
they continued to live together.

522
00:38:22,822 --> 00:38:25,408
It's not that good. Your gimbap is better.

523
00:38:31,330 --> 00:38:34,959
And her stepmother is in Japan for work.

524
00:38:57,440 --> 00:38:59,859
It's okay, just take a seat. I'll do it.

525
00:39:22,173 --> 00:39:26,427
We need to have her move before reporters
find out she's living in such a place

526
00:39:27,011 --> 00:39:29,597
and probably have her cut ties
with her grandmother too.

527
00:39:29,680 --> 00:39:32,850
I'll call her and tell her
to move out as soon as…

528
00:39:33,767 --> 00:39:34,894
Don't call her.

529
00:39:34,977 --> 00:39:36,437
I don't want anyone calling her.

530
00:39:36,520 --> 00:39:38,230
-I'll do it myself.
-Okay.

531
00:39:41,066 --> 00:39:42,067
Where's Mi-ran?

532
00:39:42,151 --> 00:39:44,195
She said she had plans
with Director Lee Jun-hwan tonight.

533
00:39:44,278 --> 00:39:45,905
She should be with him right now.

534
00:39:45,988 --> 00:39:47,907
Tell her not to drink
and to go home early.

535
00:39:48,532 --> 00:39:49,533
Understood.

536
00:40:12,598 --> 00:40:13,974
I'm on my way now.

537
00:40:14,058 --> 00:40:15,643
Yes, I'm in the car.

538
00:40:17,353 --> 00:40:18,729
She's the one who's in trouble.

539
00:40:18,812 --> 00:40:20,105
Take your time reading this.

540
00:40:21,607 --> 00:40:24,109
-Let's meet up again. Promise?
-Okay.

541
00:40:24,693 --> 00:40:26,195
Yes, of course. We promise.

542
00:40:26,278 --> 00:40:28,280
Get home safely.

543
00:40:28,364 --> 00:40:30,074
Have a good night.

544
00:40:30,157 --> 00:40:32,034
-Good night.
-Bye!

545
00:40:32,117 --> 00:40:33,202
-See you again!
-Okay.

546
00:40:46,590 --> 00:40:48,467
Let's share a taxi. I'll drop you off.

547
00:40:51,095 --> 00:40:52,137
Let's go together!

548
00:41:11,740 --> 00:41:14,743
The 46th Korean Film Awards
Best New Director Award goes to…

549
00:41:16,203 --> 00:41:18,831
Hwang Dong-man for Weather Maker!

550
00:42:02,750 --> 00:42:03,709
Hey, Ax.

551
00:42:05,544 --> 00:42:07,630
I hear you'll be working
with Hwang Dong-man.

552
00:42:09,089 --> 00:42:10,966
You're on my payroll,

553
00:42:12,343 --> 00:42:13,969
but you're taking work from outside?

554
00:42:15,346 --> 00:42:18,432
You know that many people
ask me to review their screenplays.

555
00:42:19,099 --> 00:42:20,768
That doesn't even count as work.

556
00:42:21,352 --> 00:42:22,353
Hwang Dong-man

557
00:42:23,228 --> 00:42:26,398
was under CEO Ko Hye-jin's wing
for ten years before she gave up.

558
00:42:27,107 --> 00:42:29,276
You think she gave up
because she's not as good as you?

559
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:31,445
For the love of god, Ax.

560
00:42:31,528 --> 00:42:33,614
Stop digging through other people's trash.

561
00:42:34,531 --> 00:42:37,159
You only review screenplays
that are seconds from the shredder.

562
00:42:37,242 --> 00:42:40,537
I bet you only support the underdog team
when you watch sports.

563
00:42:41,705 --> 00:42:43,707
You think your workplace
is where you build your humanity?

564
00:42:44,583 --> 00:42:45,959
You think that's what I'm paying you for?

565
00:42:46,794 --> 00:42:49,963
If we only work with directors
who have already proven themselves,

566
00:42:50,714 --> 00:42:53,634
who will discover
the breakout rookie directors?

567
00:42:53,717 --> 00:42:55,761
You don't have to do that!

568
00:42:55,844 --> 00:43:00,099
People who have money
just focus on those who are a sure bet.

569
00:43:00,182 --> 00:43:03,060
Only people with no money
go around digging through trash.

570
00:43:03,769 --> 00:43:04,812
When you get to my age,

571
00:43:05,396 --> 00:43:07,356
you can just tell at a glance

572
00:43:08,315 --> 00:43:10,275
who's going to make it and who won't.

573
00:43:10,859 --> 00:43:13,862
There's no such thing
as a tragic genius or a hidden expert.

574
00:43:13,946 --> 00:43:17,032
Money just follows people
who are destined to make money.

575
00:43:17,116 --> 00:43:18,909
They can't hide from it
even if they wanted to.

576
00:43:18,992 --> 00:43:20,119
Do you see me hiding?

577
00:43:21,161 --> 00:43:24,039
So stop rummaging through trash!

578
00:43:28,127 --> 00:43:28,961
Throw them all out.

579
00:43:30,212 --> 00:43:32,131
How frustrating.

580
00:43:34,591 --> 00:43:38,095
Why would a successful director
work with small fries like us?

581
00:43:41,515 --> 00:43:43,308
I don't get it.

582
00:43:45,686 --> 00:43:48,647
I can't credit you as a writer.
I'll list you as a development producer.

583
00:43:48,731 --> 00:43:49,732
That's the best I can do.

584
00:43:58,532 --> 00:43:59,992
Are you kidding me?

585
00:44:04,121 --> 00:44:05,998
Stop leaving me on read,

586
00:44:06,081 --> 00:44:08,250
or else I'll show up at your place
and turn it upside down.

587
00:44:16,925 --> 00:44:18,802
I wish I had an older brother.

588
00:44:20,804 --> 00:44:22,473
A crazy-ass older brother.

589
00:44:34,151 --> 00:44:35,778
The wedding is right around the corner.

590
00:44:35,861 --> 00:44:39,740
I need a straight answer
on whether you've booked someone or not.

591
00:44:39,823 --> 00:44:41,492
I've called you dozens of times.

592
00:44:42,075 --> 00:44:43,035
What are you going to do?

593
00:44:43,660 --> 00:44:45,120
I bragged to the in-laws

594
00:44:45,204 --> 00:44:47,623
that a famous singer
would perform the wedding song.

595
00:44:47,706 --> 00:44:49,249
Am I supposed to tell them
it's not happening anymore?

596
00:44:49,333 --> 00:44:50,876
I'll lose face!

597
00:44:50,959 --> 00:44:54,338
You've been in that industry for 20 years,
and you have no one to ask?

598
00:44:57,883 --> 00:44:59,510
WEATHER MAKER

599
00:45:05,891 --> 00:45:08,018
MA JAE-YEONG, YOU PIECE OF SHIT

600
00:45:17,945 --> 00:45:20,572
MA JAE-YEONG'S "KNOCK, KNOCK, KNOCK"
AWARDED KFA'S GRANT

601
00:45:22,699 --> 00:45:24,701
…A PSYCHOLOGICAL FANTASY
THAT OPENS A THOUSAND DOORS…

602
00:45:27,496 --> 00:45:29,957
A THOUSAND DOORS

603
00:45:31,291 --> 00:45:33,001
Can you get me Ma Jae-yeong's screenplay?

604
00:45:34,378 --> 00:45:36,213
He'll show it to you if you ask.

605
00:45:36,880 --> 00:45:39,591
Or maybe you can ask Hye-jin.

606
00:45:40,926 --> 00:45:42,594
I just need to check something.

607
00:45:43,929 --> 00:45:45,264
That piece of shit.

608
00:45:45,347 --> 00:45:47,474
KNOCK KNOCK KNOCK

609
00:45:47,558 --> 00:45:48,684
For as long as I can remember,

610
00:45:49,685 --> 00:45:53,105
I've never seen people as just people.
I saw them as masses.

611
00:45:53,188 --> 00:45:54,565
Masses of emotion.

612
00:45:54,648 --> 00:45:57,109
PEOPLE ARE ALL… MASSES OF EMOTION

613
00:46:00,153 --> 00:46:01,196
You seem like someone

614
00:46:01,780 --> 00:46:04,575
who's got all thousand doors wide open.

615
00:46:04,658 --> 00:46:06,493
JI-WON: (MUTTERING) A THOUSAND DOORS…

616
00:46:21,383 --> 00:46:22,801
Don't you think we should meet?

617
00:46:23,635 --> 00:46:24,553
Why?

618
00:46:25,304 --> 00:46:26,597
Just tell me over the phone.

619
00:46:26,680 --> 00:46:28,765
If you don't come out,
I'm going to Ko Hye-jin.

620
00:46:29,808 --> 00:46:30,767
Want me to do that?

621
00:46:35,272 --> 00:46:37,149
Fucking hell.

622
00:46:38,025 --> 00:46:39,568
Fucking what?

623
00:46:41,153 --> 00:46:43,780
I should be the one swearing, you bastard.

624
00:46:44,781 --> 00:46:47,784
Have you ever seen someone
who's got all thousand doors wide open?

625
00:46:47,868 --> 00:46:49,828
Mine are all open.

626
00:46:49,911 --> 00:46:51,622
You're in real trouble, you punk.

627
00:46:52,539 --> 00:46:57,252
Forcing myself to read your writing
back in the day has finally paid off.

628
00:46:57,336 --> 00:46:59,755
So this is how I catch you, huh?

629
00:47:00,797 --> 00:47:02,090
I told you, didn't I?

630
00:47:02,174 --> 00:47:04,384
When you read someone's work,
you can see right through them.

631
00:47:04,968 --> 00:47:06,345
Like what they're thinking,

632
00:47:06,428 --> 00:47:09,431
what kind of person they are,
or how they've lived.

633
00:47:10,057 --> 00:47:12,267
So tell me this.

634
00:47:13,101 --> 00:47:14,853
Why am I seeing Byeon Eun-a
in your writing?

635
00:47:15,646 --> 00:47:16,730
Because we dated.

636
00:47:19,650 --> 00:47:21,318
I dated Byeon Eun-a.

637
00:47:22,152 --> 00:47:24,321
I know, you bastard!
I can see it in your writing!

638
00:47:24,905 --> 00:47:26,698
But why isn't she credited
on the screenplay?

639
00:47:27,282 --> 00:47:30,702
Do I have to credit every little help
I got from someone I was dating?

640
00:47:31,328 --> 00:47:33,914
Writing is like blood, so you can't
transfuse it unless it's the same type.

641
00:47:34,706 --> 00:47:35,916
It clots and tangles.

642
00:47:35,999 --> 00:47:39,252
Your screenplay clearly has two people
with different blood types in it.

643
00:47:39,753 --> 00:47:41,922
Sharp and precise Byeon Eun-a,

644
00:47:42,005 --> 00:47:44,257
and dull, old-fashioned Ma Jae-yeong.

645
00:47:44,341 --> 00:47:47,427
I could go through your screenplay
and precisely pick out who wrote what,

646
00:47:47,511 --> 00:47:49,304
without making a single mistake.

647
00:47:49,388 --> 00:47:50,389
Want me to do that?

648
00:47:51,598 --> 00:47:53,016
You think I'm the only one who can tell?

649
00:47:53,642 --> 00:47:56,061
I'll bet my life Ko Hye-jin knows too.

650
00:47:58,105 --> 00:48:00,357
You stole from someone you shouldn't have.

651
00:48:00,857 --> 00:48:02,693
You stole from a genius, you bastard.

652
00:48:02,776 --> 00:48:06,113
You stole from someone
who shines like a jewel.

653
00:48:06,196 --> 00:48:10,158
Someone so unmistakably bright
there's no way you wouldn't know it's her.

654
00:48:10,242 --> 00:48:11,743
But what did you say?

655
00:48:12,577 --> 00:48:13,829
You don't like her work?

656
00:48:15,747 --> 00:48:17,916
She only goes for duds
about to get tossed?

657
00:48:19,918 --> 00:48:21,128
You call that manners?

658
00:48:23,171 --> 00:48:25,006
Unlike you, that shining woman

659
00:48:25,757 --> 00:48:27,759
sets aside her own greed and desire

660
00:48:27,843 --> 00:48:29,886
and picks up the ones
that are about to get scrapped.

661
00:48:30,595 --> 00:48:32,889
Isn't it remarkable
that she uses her talent

662
00:48:32,973 --> 00:48:35,016
for what others would toss out?

663
00:48:35,851 --> 00:48:38,186
-You should put her on a pedestal!
-Goddamn it!

664
00:48:39,479 --> 00:48:41,189
Save your lecture
until you've proven yourself.

665
00:48:42,524 --> 00:48:45,402
You know what I realized
when you gave me so much crap?

666
00:48:46,319 --> 00:48:49,197
"I see. I remind this guy of himself."

667
00:48:49,948 --> 00:48:51,491
"He hates himself right now."

668
00:48:52,284 --> 00:48:55,162
You despised me
for being as incompetent as you

669
00:48:55,787 --> 00:48:57,247
and belittled me.

670
00:49:01,460 --> 00:49:02,627
You really think

671
00:49:04,045 --> 00:49:05,464
I'm still as incompetent as you?

672
00:49:12,512 --> 00:49:16,224
DIRECTOR HWANG DONG-MAN

673
00:49:40,332 --> 00:49:42,000
You said you'd text me.

674
00:49:59,601 --> 00:50:00,727
Thank you.

675
00:50:02,270 --> 00:50:03,605
Thanks to you,

676
00:50:04,356 --> 00:50:06,483
my watch turned green
for the first time today.

677
00:50:16,284 --> 00:50:17,202
Same here.

678
00:50:18,745 --> 00:50:20,622
Mine just turned green
for the first time today too.

679
00:51:18,388 --> 00:51:19,681
Jeez, who is it?

680
00:51:26,646 --> 00:51:28,189
My goodness.

681
00:51:29,900 --> 00:51:30,734
Hello?

682
00:51:32,861 --> 00:51:33,820
Are you sleeping?

683
00:51:34,738 --> 00:51:35,822
Yeah.

684
00:51:37,073 --> 00:51:38,199
Okay, go back to sleep.

685
00:51:38,909 --> 00:51:40,076
It's better that you sleep.

686
00:51:42,245 --> 00:51:43,955
Just listen as you sleep.

687
00:51:45,498 --> 00:51:46,416
Yeong-su.

688
00:51:47,083 --> 00:51:48,043
What?

689
00:51:48,793 --> 00:51:51,254
Why are you answering? Go back to sleep.

690
00:51:51,922 --> 00:51:53,006
Just go to sleep.

691
00:51:55,926 --> 00:51:57,344
I'll just talk to myself.

692
00:51:59,638 --> 00:52:01,765
This is embarrassing,
so I'll talk to myself.

693
00:52:01,848 --> 00:52:02,891
Go back to sleep.

694
00:52:05,268 --> 00:52:06,394
Yeong-su.

695
00:52:16,446 --> 00:52:18,573
Nobody knows about this.

696
00:52:20,533 --> 00:52:22,535
Not even Hye-jin.

697
00:52:24,913 --> 00:52:27,415
It's a secret I'm taking to my grave.

698
00:52:28,917 --> 00:52:31,294
THE LUSTFUL BOTTLE OPENER

699
00:52:31,378 --> 00:52:34,047
You know my debut film,
The Lustful Bottle Opener?

700
00:52:34,130 --> 00:52:35,006
That was actually…

701
00:52:39,344 --> 00:52:40,720
about Dong-man.

702
00:52:48,561 --> 00:52:50,939
When we lived together back in college,

703
00:52:51,898 --> 00:52:53,650
he came home totally wasted one day.

704
00:52:54,609 --> 00:52:57,946
He said he'd given a bottle opener
as a gift to a girl he liked,

705
00:52:59,447 --> 00:53:02,784
but he saw it on Cheol-ho's fridge
and totally lost it.

706
00:53:03,910 --> 00:53:06,746
He said he tore the door off the fridge.

707
00:53:07,706 --> 00:53:10,333
He was drunk and rambling on and on,

708
00:53:11,334 --> 00:53:13,003
and I wanted to write it all down.

709
00:53:15,839 --> 00:53:18,216
Because everything he said
as he was flipping out was hilarious.

710
00:53:22,512 --> 00:53:24,222
I lay down to go to sleep,

711
00:53:25,598 --> 00:53:28,435
but scenes started unfolding
before my eyes.

712
00:53:29,519 --> 00:53:30,729
A lackey in a gang

713
00:53:31,730 --> 00:53:34,482
gave a bottle opener as a gift
to a woman he liked…

714
00:53:34,566 --> 00:53:35,692
Monte Cristo.

715
00:53:38,153 --> 00:53:40,572
…but sees it on his boss's fridge.

716
00:53:41,865 --> 00:53:43,158
I knew it'd be a hit.

717
00:53:43,241 --> 00:53:44,492
I wrote it in three days.

718
00:53:45,368 --> 00:53:47,537
After that, I couldn't sleep
because it was too good.

719
00:53:49,164 --> 00:53:50,832
I kept thinking,
"This is Dong-man's story."

720
00:53:50,915 --> 00:53:53,126
"What if he says
he wants to write it himself?"

721
00:53:55,003 --> 00:53:56,254
But that idiot…

722
00:53:59,299 --> 00:54:00,550
didn't remember anything.

723
00:54:03,053 --> 00:54:05,805
He was so drunk that he blacked out.

724
00:54:06,973 --> 00:54:09,642
I've been on pins and needles ever since.

725
00:54:12,145 --> 00:54:13,980
Even during the premiere,

726
00:54:14,064 --> 00:54:16,775
I was afraid he'd suddenly remember
while watching it.

727
00:54:17,275 --> 00:54:18,401
Goddamn it.

728
00:54:19,027 --> 00:54:21,029
I hoped he'd just die in an accident.

729
00:54:23,698 --> 00:54:24,949
That's when I started

730
00:54:26,409 --> 00:54:27,994
to act snarky toward him.

731
00:54:33,208 --> 00:54:34,250
You already know…

732
00:54:36,669 --> 00:54:37,670
I'm sick of hearing

733
00:54:39,339 --> 00:54:42,634
that my debut film is my best work.

734
00:54:45,386 --> 00:54:47,013
Whenever I hear that…

735
00:54:51,142 --> 00:54:53,686
But if Dong-man suddenly gets his debut,

736
00:54:54,729 --> 00:54:56,648
and his film is actually good…

737
00:54:58,983 --> 00:54:59,901
Then…

738
00:55:04,572 --> 00:55:06,407
That'd make me nothing.

739
00:55:08,535 --> 00:55:09,410
That's why…

740
00:55:13,164 --> 00:55:15,792
I wished that the bastard
would never debut.

741
00:55:18,336 --> 00:55:20,296
I hoped he'd just disappear.

742
00:55:24,926 --> 00:55:26,136
Dong-man

743
00:55:26,845 --> 00:55:28,555
never showed it in front of you,

744
00:55:30,598 --> 00:55:32,559
but he really liked
The Lustful Bottle Opener.

745
00:55:33,977 --> 00:55:35,145
He liked it so much

746
00:55:35,812 --> 00:55:37,730
that he said he could almost kiss you.

747
00:55:40,024 --> 00:55:42,777
He said he wanted to make a film like it
before he died.

748
00:55:45,363 --> 00:55:46,614
That's how much he loved it.

749
00:56:03,256 --> 00:56:04,340
Were you awake?

750
00:56:09,554 --> 00:56:10,555
Why aren't you sleeping?

751
00:56:12,557 --> 00:56:14,058
Jeez, why aren't you sleeping?

752
00:56:16,311 --> 00:56:18,188
There's no need to be so on edge.

753
00:56:19,731 --> 00:56:23,067
We all use other people's stories
all the time.

754
00:56:24,777 --> 00:56:28,156
Even if you had told Dong-man,
he wouldn't have made it work.

755
00:56:29,073 --> 00:56:31,868
How many good stories has he let slip by?

756
00:56:34,370 --> 00:56:36,122
If he just wrote about his own stories,

757
00:56:36,831 --> 00:56:38,499
he'd have made three or four films by now.

758
00:56:40,376 --> 00:56:42,212
He doesn't realize
how good his stories are

759
00:56:43,171 --> 00:56:44,923
and keeps trying to force something out.

760
00:57:08,238 --> 00:57:09,155
Gyeong-se.

761
00:57:10,740 --> 00:57:12,367
It must've been really hard for you.

762
00:57:14,827 --> 00:57:16,079
That was a beautiful confession.

763
00:57:17,747 --> 00:57:19,165
You deserve a round of applause.

764
00:57:30,718 --> 00:57:33,054
HWANG DONG-MAN AND HIS BROTHER
NOT ALLOWED

765
00:57:33,137 --> 00:57:34,180
Is there anyone here

766
00:57:34,931 --> 00:57:36,766
who hasn't written about Dong-man?

767
00:57:38,309 --> 00:57:39,185
Ki-ri.

768
00:57:40,144 --> 00:57:43,648
The troublemaking brother-in-law
in X-Family is Dong-man, right?

769
00:57:45,108 --> 00:57:46,109
Seung-tae.

770
00:57:46,818 --> 00:57:48,528
In You Drive Me Crazy,

771
00:57:48,611 --> 00:57:50,697
the idiot loan shark is Dong-man, right?

772
00:57:51,781 --> 00:57:55,118
Whenever Dong-man talks,
everyone's eyes light up

773
00:57:55,201 --> 00:57:56,869
at the thought of using it later.

774
00:57:57,996 --> 00:57:59,497
You know this. I know this.

775
00:58:00,206 --> 00:58:01,207
We all do.

776
00:58:01,833 --> 00:58:03,001
Hey, Woo Seung-tae.

777
00:58:03,668 --> 00:58:06,754
You just openly take notes on your phone.

778
00:58:06,838 --> 00:58:08,423
That day when he went from ER to ER,

779
00:58:08,506 --> 00:58:10,967
threw up, and made a scene
trying to fish out a 500-won coin.

780
00:58:12,135 --> 00:58:14,554
You really think
no one will write about it?

781
00:58:16,472 --> 00:58:17,307
Hey, Gyeong-se.

782
00:58:18,224 --> 00:58:20,184
That story about
the National Stress Management Department.

783
00:58:20,268 --> 00:58:21,728
Can you finish that without Dong-man?

784
00:58:24,105 --> 00:58:25,356
I want you to think about

785
00:58:26,274 --> 00:58:30,278
how many ideas he's given us
while driving us up the wall.

786
00:58:31,362 --> 00:58:32,238
Just think.

787
00:58:33,489 --> 00:58:34,490
Now tell me…

788
00:58:36,576 --> 00:58:37,785
if we should still get rid of him.

789
00:58:40,288 --> 00:58:42,874
We're all relieved
because he's so clueless

790
00:58:42,957 --> 00:58:46,794
and doesn't even realize we're using him.

791
00:58:46,878 --> 00:58:48,087
But we still feel guilty,

792
00:58:49,088 --> 00:58:50,298
so we get snarky with him.

793
00:58:52,592 --> 00:58:53,468
Am I wrong?

794
00:58:54,802 --> 00:58:58,681
Do you think you can come up with ideas
without Dong-man?

795
00:59:01,392 --> 00:59:02,226
Okay, then.

796
00:59:03,478 --> 00:59:05,480
Do I get to have Hwang Dong-man to myself?

797
00:59:06,356 --> 00:59:07,190
Huh?

798
00:59:08,983 --> 00:59:09,859
Fine.

799
00:59:10,818 --> 00:59:12,570
Starting today, I'm his best friend.

800
00:59:13,154 --> 00:59:15,490
Everything that happens to him
is mine to write about.

801
00:59:15,573 --> 00:59:17,784
You can't use any of them
without my permission.

802
00:59:19,661 --> 00:59:20,745
Come on, Yeong-su.

803
00:59:22,246 --> 00:59:25,124
That's not how you end a scene.

804
00:59:26,292 --> 00:59:28,878
You know I'm not good at endings.

805
00:59:30,672 --> 00:59:33,257
I've already revised the ending 27 times.

806
00:59:35,426 --> 00:59:36,761
Whatever.

807
00:59:37,512 --> 00:59:38,346
In any case,

808
00:59:38,846 --> 00:59:40,014
Hwang Dong-man is mine.

809
00:59:40,640 --> 00:59:42,433
I'm old and don't have any ideas.

810
00:59:43,017 --> 00:59:44,018
Hwang Dong-man…

811
00:59:45,311 --> 00:59:46,437
Hwang Dong-man is mine.

812
00:59:51,859 --> 00:59:53,236
Why aren't you saying anything?

813
00:59:57,365 --> 00:59:58,408
Not you.

814
00:59:59,701 --> 01:00:02,120
I'm sure you have a lot to say.

815
01:00:06,958 --> 01:00:07,959
I'm against it.

816
01:00:09,502 --> 01:00:11,879
I'm against Director Hwang
rejoining The Eight Club.

817
01:00:15,174 --> 01:00:16,968
I don't want him seeing anyone but me.

818
01:00:17,677 --> 01:00:18,511
Why?

819
01:00:19,262 --> 01:00:20,304
You want him for yourself too?

820
01:00:21,097 --> 01:00:21,931
Yes.

821
01:00:22,724 --> 01:00:23,891
I want him all to myself

822
01:00:25,393 --> 01:00:28,604
and then give everything back to him.

823
01:00:29,313 --> 01:00:30,231
So he can see…

824
01:00:34,277 --> 01:00:37,447
how brilliant he really is.

825
01:00:56,549 --> 01:00:58,551
Why didn't you tell me you've got a girl?

826
01:00:59,969 --> 01:01:00,803
What?

827
01:01:01,387 --> 01:01:03,639
I told you I'd lift the ban
when you get a girlfriend.

828
01:01:06,559 --> 01:01:08,561
It's a one-way crush.

829
01:01:08,644 --> 01:01:10,980
Hey, don't spread any rumors.

830
01:01:11,063 --> 01:01:12,398
If Eun-a finds out…

831
01:01:13,524 --> 01:01:15,318
Don't, okay? I'm serious.

832
01:01:15,401 --> 01:01:16,819
It's not one-sided.

833
01:01:16,903 --> 01:01:18,529
She's openly taking your side.

834
01:01:21,073 --> 01:01:22,325
You're no longer banned.

835
01:01:27,288 --> 01:01:29,582
HWANG DONG-MAN AND HIS BROTHER
NOT ALLOWED

836
01:01:29,665 --> 01:01:31,209
Goodness me.

837
01:02:06,077 --> 01:02:08,412
That idiot better not go up there
and sing himself.

838
01:02:08,496 --> 01:02:10,081
I'll drag him off the stage.

839
01:02:11,666 --> 01:02:14,210
Please welcome the guest singer
with a big round of applause.

840
01:02:14,794 --> 01:02:15,628
Now,

841
01:02:16,420 --> 01:02:17,255
the wedding song.

842
01:02:30,142 --> 01:02:31,769
I'd like to congratulate

843
01:02:31,853 --> 01:02:34,730
Director Hwang Dong-man's cousin,
Ms. Lee Ye-rin,

844
01:02:34,814 --> 01:02:37,900
and her groom, Mr. Kim Sin-yeong,
on their wedding.

845
01:02:37,984 --> 01:02:40,111
I'd also like to thank
Director Hwang Dong-man

846
01:02:40,194 --> 01:02:44,657
for healing my arm that got injured
while filming Sister Vengeance.

847
01:02:44,740 --> 01:02:45,658
Director Hwang,

848
01:02:45,741 --> 01:02:49,537
don't forget I'm first in line
for your next amazing screenplay.

849
01:02:50,371 --> 01:02:52,331
Now for the wedding song.

850
01:02:55,251 --> 01:02:58,963
Excuse me, just a moment
We're still strangers for now

851
01:02:59,046 --> 01:03:02,884
But soon enough
We'll be an addictive game

852
01:03:02,967 --> 01:03:07,221
This feeling I'm feeling right now
Like it's connecting us

853
01:03:07,305 --> 01:03:10,433
Like ice cream that's melting away

854
01:03:10,516 --> 01:03:13,269
Right now, this feels like a dream

855
01:03:13,352 --> 01:03:17,189
You and me, dancing together

856
01:03:17,273 --> 01:03:20,860
The feeling is so incredible
It's like art

857
01:03:20,943 --> 01:03:24,739
Ooh-eh-oh, ooh-eh-oh, ooh-eh-oh

858
01:03:30,161 --> 01:03:32,788
I'm not even hoping for success.

859
01:03:35,082 --> 01:03:36,918
I just want to make one film.

860
01:03:38,753 --> 01:03:42,548
So I can overcome this feeling
of worthlessness, even just a little.

861
01:04:22,588 --> 01:04:24,382
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

862
01:04:42,483 --> 01:04:44,568
I should've fallen in love.

863
01:04:44,652 --> 01:04:47,571
Who knew I had
such a powerful engine inside me?

864
01:04:47,655 --> 01:04:49,240
I should've fallen in love.

865
01:04:49,323 --> 01:04:52,576
Byeon Eun-a can revive dead scripts,
and now she's backing Hwang Dong-man.

866
01:04:52,660 --> 01:04:54,161
Think this through.

867
01:04:54,245 --> 01:04:55,705
Another person came forward.

868
01:04:55,788 --> 01:04:57,498
There's even a photo
from when she was young.

869
01:04:57,581 --> 01:05:00,835
Excuse me.
Please answer Ms. Oh Jeong-hui's call.

870
01:05:00,918 --> 01:05:02,795
Forget it. I'll tell them myself.

871
01:05:02,878 --> 01:05:04,880
On live TV, in front of the whole country.

872
01:05:04,964 --> 01:05:07,341
They showed the same pattern as you again.

873
01:05:07,425 --> 01:05:09,677
I've never gotten an "unknown."

874
01:05:09,760 --> 01:05:10,803
Why does…

875
01:05:11,387 --> 01:05:13,097
Why does that person feel that way?

876
01:05:13,180 --> 01:05:17,935
Subtitle translation by: Jenny Kim
